quran[9]{c,v,t}:
  34,23,"Intercession is of no avail with Him, except for those whom He permits. When fear is lifted from their hearts, they say, ‘What did your Lord say?’ They say, ‘The truth, and He is the All-exalted, the All-great.’"
  34,24,"Say, ‘Who provides for you from the heavens and the earth?’ Say, ‘Allah! Indeed either we or you are rightly guided or in manifest error.’"
  34,25,"Say, ‘You will not be questioned about our guilt, nor shall we be questioned about what you do.’"
  34,26,"Say, ‘Our Lord will bring us together, then He will judge between us with justice, and He is the All-knowing Judge.’"
  34,27,"Say, ‘Show me those whom you associate with Him as partners.’ No! [They can never show any such partner]. Indeed, He is Allah, the All-mighty, the All-wise"
  34,28,"We did not send you except as a bearer of good news and warner to all mankind, but most people do not know"
  34,29,"They say, ‘When will this promise be fulfilled, if you are truthful?’"
  34,30,"Say, ‘Your promised hour is a day that you shall neither defer nor advance by an hour.’"
  34,31,"The faithless say, ‘We will never believe in this Quran, nor in what was [revealed] before it.’ But if you were to see when the wrongdoers will be made to stop before their Lord casting the blame on one another. Those who were abased will say to those who were arrogant, ‘Had it not been for you, we would surely have been faithful.’"